==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scourer
<hw>Scour"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, scours.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A rover or footpad; a prowling robber.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In those days of highwaymen and <qex>scourers</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scourge</ent>⟦br⟧
